
ID: 10
Title: Saving the preferences in ‘My Profile’.

Priority:
High 

Prerequisites:
Making sure that the cookies are enabled.

Test type:
Positive (+)

Environment:
Windows 10, Chrome  80.0.3987.149

Description:
The test describes a results of positive transition of  the preferences to ‘ My Profile’.

Test scenario:
    1.Open the job search application.
    2.Select in the Jobs section - ‘Job age’: only today.
    3.Select in the Jobs section - ‘Distance’: within 25 miles.
    4.Select in the Results section -’ How many’: 20 jobs.
    5.Select in the Language section - ‘-Korean’. 
    6.Click ‘Save preferences’.
    7.Complete the preference name - ‘My Second Choice’.
    8.A message is displayed on a green background: The preferences has been saved.
    9.The preferences have been saved in ‘My Profile’ as a ‘My second choice’.

The expected results:
    1.The job search application is opened.
    2.Only today is selected in the Job age section.
    3.Within 25 miles is selected in the Distance section.
    4.20 jobs is selected in the Results section.
    5.Korean is selected in the Language section.
    6.The button ‘Save preferences’ is clicked.
    7.‘My Second Choice’ is completed the preference name.
    8.‘The preferences has been saved’ is displayed on a green background.
    9.The preferences have been saved in My profile as ‘My second choice’.
